          id: "practice",
          title: "Practice Session Structure",
          content: "<h4>Session 1:</h4><ul><li>Minutes 0-25: Learn theory - understand natural minor scale, three types, relative relationships</li><li>Minutes 25-55: Exercise 1 &amp; 2 - learn minor scale shapes, compare the three types</li><li>Minutes 55-75: Ear training - major vs minor key recognition</li><li>Minutes 75-90: Free exploration - find minor scales in songs you know</li></ul><h4>Session 2:</h4><ul><li>Minutes 0-20: Review theory - build minor scales from different roots</li><li>Minutes 20-50: Exercise 3 - explore relative major/minor relationships on guitar</li><li>Minutes 50-70: Ear training - three minor scale sounds</li><li>Minutes 70-90: Application - learn a song in a minor key</li></ul><h4>Session 3:</h4><ul><li>Minutes 0-20: Exercise 4 - minor chord progressions</li><li>Minutes 20-50: Practice progressions smoothly in multiple keys</li><li>Minutes 50-75: Ear training - song analysis, i-V resolution test</li><li>Minutes 75-90: Integration - improvise over a minor backing track</li></ul>"
