          content: "<h4>Session 1:</h4><ul><li>Minutes 0-25: Learn theory - chord tone soloing, pentatonic scales</li><li>Minutes 25-55: Exercise 1 &amp; 2 - chord tone targeting, pentatonic patterns</li><li>Minutes 55-75: Ear training - sing then play</li><li>Minutes 75-90: Free improvisation over backing track (focus on chord tones)</li></ul><h4>Session 2:</h4><ul><li>Minutes 0-20: Review theory - blues scale, phrasing concepts</li><li>Minutes 20-50: Exercise 3 &amp; 4 - blues scale with bends, call and response</li><li>Minutes 50-70: Ear training - transcription practice</li><li>Minutes 70-90: Application - learn a simple solo by ear</li></ul><h4>Session 3:</h4><ul><li>Minutes 0-25: Exercise 5 - motif development</li><li>Minutes 25-55: Practice improvising with motifs over backing track</li><li>Minutes 55-75: Ear training - chord tone ear training, imitation game</li><li>Minutes 75-90: Integration - record yourself improvising, listen back critically</li></ul>"
