      importantNote: "<h4>The Rhythm Guitarist's Mindset</h4><p>Remember: The rhythm guitarist is the foundation. Bass and drums lock in with YOU. If your rhythm is shaky, the whole band suffers.</p><p><strong>Great rhythm playing is:</strong></p><ul><li>Consistent</li><li>Groovy</li><li>Dynamically interesting</li><li>In service of the song</li></ul><p><strong>Bad rhythm playing is:</strong></p><ul><li>Rushing or dragging</li><li>Monotonous (no dynamics)</li><li>Sloppy chord changes</li><li>Ignoring the groove</li></ul><p>Focus on being a rock-solid rhythm player. It's more important than flashy solos.</p>",
