          content: "<h4>Exercise 1: Chord Progression Creation</h4><p>Create 3 original progressions:</p><p><strong>Progression 1: Bright and Happy (Major Key)</strong></p><ul><li>Use I, IV, V, vi</li><li>Example: C - F - Am - G</li></ul><p><strong>Progression 2: Dark and Moody (Minor Key)</strong></p><ul><li>Use i, iv, VI, VII</li><li>Example: Am - Dm - F - G</li></ul><p><strong>Progression 3: Experimental (Borrowed Chords)</strong></p><ul><li>Mix major and minor</li><li>Example: C - Fm - Ab - G (borrowing from C minor)</li></ul><p>Play each progression until you can change chords smoothly.</p><h4>Exercise 2: Melody Over Chords</h4><p>Take Progression 1 (C - F - Am - G):</p><p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Hum/sing a simple melody over it<br><strong>Step 2:</strong> Figure out that melody on guitar (one note at a time)<br><strong>Step 3:</strong> Write it down (scale degrees or actual notes)<br><strong>Step 4:</strong> Refine - does it start and end on the root? Does it have a climax?</p><p>Do this for all 3 progressions.</p><h4>Exercise 3: Form Construction</h4><p>Build a simple song structure:</p><p><strong>Verse (8 bars):</strong> Progression 1, quieter dynamics<br><strong>Chorus (8 bars):</strong> Progression 1, louder dynamics, different melody<br><strong>Verse 2 (8 bars):</strong> Same as Verse 1<br><strong>Chorus 2 (8 bars):</strong> Same as Chorus 1<br><strong>Bridge (4 bars):</strong> Progression 2 (contrast)<br><strong>Chorus 3 (8 bars):</strong> Final chorus, biggest dynamics</p><p>Practice playing through this form smoothly.</p><h4>Exercise 4: Rhythm and Arrangement</h4><p>Take your chord progressions and add rhythmic variation:</p><p><strong>Verse:</strong> Arpeggiated (fingerpicked)<br><strong>Chorus:</strong> Strummed (full chords)<br><strong>Bridge:</strong> Simpler rhythm (half-note strums for space)</p><p>This creates dynamic contrast between sections.</p><h4>Exercise 5: Complete Composition</h4><p>Combine everything:</p><p><strong>Your Task:</strong> Write a 2-minute instrumental piece with:</p><ul><li>Intro (4 bars)</li><li>Verse (8 bars)</li><li>Chorus (8 bars)</li><li>Verse 2 (8 bars)</li><li>Chorus 2 (8 bars)</li><li>Bridge (4 bars)</li><li>Final Chorus (8 bars)</li><li>Outro (4 bars)</li></ul><p>Use original chord progressions and melodies. Vary dynamics and rhythm.</p><p><strong>Record yourself playing it.</strong></p>"
