      title: "Glossary of Terms",
      content: "<ul><li><strong>Interval:</strong> The distance between two notes</li><li><strong>Triad:</strong> A three-note chord (root, 3rd, 5th)</li><li><strong>Diatonic:</strong> Notes/chords that belong to a key</li><li><strong>Chromatic:</strong> All 12 notes (including sharps/flats)</li><li><strong>Modulation:</strong> Changing from one key to another</li><li><strong>Cadence:</strong> How a progression resolves</li><li><strong>Voice Leading:</strong> Smooth movement between chords</li><li><strong>Inversion:</strong> Rearranging chord notes (different bass note)</li><li><strong>Syncopation:</strong> Emphasizing off-beats</li><li><strong>Arpeggio:</strong> Playing chord notes one at a time</li><li><strong>Dynamics:</strong> Volume (loud/soft)</li><li><strong>Articulation:</strong> How notes are played (staccato, legato, etc.)</li></ul>"
